<TITLE> Hasina shown arrested in Niko graft case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 31 (bdnews24.com)Former prime minister Sheikh Hasina was shown arrested in the Niko corruption case, a day after another ex-prime minister, Khaleda Zia, was named arrested in a different case with similar allegations. Investigating officer SM Shabbir Hasan, also deputy director of the Anticorruption Commission, appealed to the Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court to name Hasina arrested in the case. Additional chief metropolitan magistrate Md Golam Rabbani granted the appeal. According to allegations against seven people, including Hasina, the accused cost the government Tk 13,000 crore in losses by leasing three gasfields in Bangladesh to Canadian gas exploration company Niko Resources. The co-accused of Hasina are detained former state minister for energy Rafiqul Islam, former principal secretary to the Prime Minister's Office SA Samad, former energy secretaries Dr Towfiq-e-Elahi Chowdhury and M Akmal Hossain, former Petrobangla chairman Mosharraf Hossain and Niko vice-president (South Aisa) Kashem Sharif. The case against Khaleda was filed by ACC deputy director Mahbubul Alam on similar allegations of abusing power in approving gas deals for Niko. A court Sunday ordered the police to show Khaleda and former minister Moudud Ahmed arrested in the case. bdnews24.
